---
layout: default
subject: "[{{base_id_tag}}] Certificate renewal problem for {{idTag}}"
---
<p style="font-size: 16px; color: #1f2937; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Hello {{idTag}},</p>
<p style="font-size: 14px; color: #4b5563; line-height: 1.6; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">
	We were unable to renew the TLS certificate for your {{instance_name}} tenant.
</p>

<table role="presentation" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" border="0" width="100%" style="margin: 20px 0; background-color: #f9fafb; border-radius: 6px;">
	<tr>
		<td style="padding: 15px 20px;">
			<p style="font-size: 13px; color: #1f2937; margin: 0 0 8px 0;"><strong>Domain:</strong> {{domain}}</p>
			<p style="font-size: 13px; color: #1f2937; margin: 0 0 8px 0;"><strong>Expires at:</strong> {{expiresAt}}</p>
			<p style="font-size: 13px; color: #1f2937; margin: 0 0 8px 0;"><strong>Days to expiry:</strong> {{daysUntilExpiry}}</p>
			<p style="font-size: 13px; color: #1f2937; margin: 0;"><strong>Reason:</strong> {{errorReason}}</p>
		</td>
	</tr>
</table>

{{#if suspended}}
<table role="presentation" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" border="0" width="100%" style="margin: 20px 0;">
	<tr>
		<td style="background-color: #fee2e2; border: 1px solid #fca5a5; border-radius: 6px; padding: 15px;">
			<p style="font-size: 13px; color: #991b1b; margin: 0;">
				<strong>Your tenant has been suspended.</strong> The certificate has expired
				and renewal is still failing, so HTTPS access to your tenant is currently
				broken. As soon as a renewal succeeds, the suspension will be lifted
				automatically.
			</p>
		</td>
	</tr>
</table>
{{/if}}

<h3 style="font-size: 16px; color: #1f2937; margin: 24px 0 12px 0;">What you need to do</h3>
<p style="font-size: 14px; color: #4b5563; line-height: 1.6; margin: 0 0 12px 0;">
	The most common cause is incorrect DNS. Make sure these DNS records point
	at this server:
</p>
<ul style="font-size: 14px; color: #4b5563; line-height: 1.6; margin: 0 0 12px 20px; padding: 0;">
	<li><code>cl-o.{{idTag}}</code> &mdash; the API domain</li>
	<li><code>{{idTag}}</code> &mdash; the app domain</li>
</ul>
<p style="font-size: 14px; color: #4b5563; line-height: 1.6; margin: 0 0 12px 0;">
	Both should resolve to: <code>{{localAddress}}</code>
</p>
<p style="font-size: 14px; color: #4b5563; line-height: 1.6; margin: 0 0 12px 0;">
	Either A records (for IP addresses) or CNAME records (for hostnames) work,
	as long as the final answer matches one of the addresses above.
</p>
<p style="font-size: 14px; color: #4b5563; line-height: 1.6; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">
	Once DNS is corrected, the next nightly renewal run will pick it up
	automatically. If the certificate has not yet expired, you have until then
	to fix it without further interruption.
</p>

<p style="font-size: 14px; color: #4b5563; line-height: 1.6; margin: 0;">
	If you continue to have problems, please contact your instance administrator.
</p>
